Methods
Anthropometric measurements and Blood Pressure of 340 eligible patients with type 2 DM recruited into the study were taken. Participants’ FPG, FLP and glycated haemoglobin were also estimated. Cardiovascular risk score was calculated using the United Kingdom Prospective Diabetes Study (UKPDS) risk engine. Diagnosis of the MS was the International Diabetes Federation Criteria (IDF).
Results
Over 66% participants had MS. The absolute cardiovascular risk score was found to be similar in persons with type 2 DM whether they fulfilled the criteria for diagnosis metabolic syndrome or not.
Conclusion
The absolute cardiovascular risk score was similar in type 2 DM patients with or without the metabolic syndrome."
}
@article{AHMAD2016S130,
title = "Glycemic and non-glycemic targets in younger and older North Indian subjects with type 2 diabetes in a Tertiary care hospital: A 10 year's retrospective data analysis",
journal = "Diabetes & Metabolic Syndrome: Clinical Research & Reviews",
volume = "10",
number = "1, Supplement 1",
